Applying technology knowledge on making copies of ethnographic items, and making reconstructions of them depending on the needs of partnership museums.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will apply textile or metalworks technology-related knowledge in copying and reconstructing ethnographic or archeological items based on the needs of partner museums.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon passing the subject, the student: - will have gained experience in preparing a copy or reconstruction of a specific (museum) item, and thus be able to take the necessary measurements of original items, treating them ethically and carefully, preparing data and drafts, select the necessary means for making a copy or reconstruction and, in preparing them, draw on the technical and mental competence amassed during the term of study
